---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import CTABlock from '../../components/CTABlock.astro';
import BlogHero from '../../components/BlogHero.astro';
import BlogFigure from '../../components/BlogFigure.astro';
import RelatedPosts from '../../components/RelatedPosts.astro';
import { business, BASE } from '../../data/business';
import { postBySlug, postsBySlugs, RELATED_POSTS } from '../../data/posts';

const post = postBySlug('cold-water-pipe-repair-galston')!;
const relatedPosts = postsBySlugs(RELATED_POSTS[post.slug] ?? []).slice(0, 3);
const siteUrl = business.siteUrl.replace(/\/$/, '');
const url = `${siteUrl}/blog/${post.slug}/`;
const ogImage = `${siteUrl}${BASE}/gallery/galston-cold-water-feed-pipe-repair-08-1600w.jpg`;

const articleSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  '@id': `${url}#article`,
  headline: post.title,
  description: post.description,
  inLanguage: 'en-GB',
  datePublished: post.date,
  dateModified: post.date,
  author: { '@type': 'Person', name: post.author, worksFor: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` } },
  publisher: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` },
  image: [ogImage],
  mainEntityOfPage: url,
  keywords: [post.keyword],
  wordCount: post.wordCount,
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`${post.title} | Sorn Handyman Services`}
  description={post.description}
  canonicalPath={`/blog/${post.slug}/`}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  ogType="article"
  extraSchema={articleSchema}
>
  <Breadcrumbs trail={[
    { name: 'Home', href: `${BASE}/` },
    { name: 'Blog', href: `${BASE}/blog/` },
    { name: post.title },
  ]} />

  <article class="container-x py-10 lg:py-14 max-w-3xl">
    <header>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-amber-600">
        <span>{post.area}</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <span class="text-navy-900/60">{post.readMinutes} min read</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <time datetime={post.date} class="text-navy-900/60">{post.dateDisplay}</time>
      </div>
      <h1 class="mt-4 font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-navy-900 leading-tight">
        {post.title}
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg text-navy-900/75">
        A cold water feed pipe repaired in an outhouse for a repeat customer
        in Galston. The sink and tap were back in action the same day.
      </p>
    </header>

    <BlogHero slug="galston-cold-water-feed-pipe-repair-08" />

    <div class="prose-sorn mt-8 text-lg cv-auto">
      <h2>What the job involved</h2>
      <p>
        Water was isolated at the stopcock before anything came apart. The
        damaged section was cut out, the run dried off and the new length of
        pipe prepped and fitted with sound joints. We held pressure on it for
        a good while before calling it done.
      </p>
      <p>
        Tap and sink were tested back on, the area dried down and everything
        tidied up. Outhouse plumbing often gets forgotten about until it
        gives up — a quick job once it is in front of you, but only if you
        can get to the pipe cleanly.
      </p>

      <BlogFigure slug="galston-cold-water-feed-pipe-repair-08" />

      <h2>Things to think about before you start</h2>
      <p>
        Know where your stopcock is before a leak starts. On most Ayrshire
        houses it is under the kitchen sink, but on older properties it can
        be in a cupboard or under the floor. Trying to find it in a panic
        with water running is not the moment.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outhouse and garage runs are the first to freeze in a cold winter.
        Lagging the exposed pipe, trickle-heating the space or fitting an
        isolator you can close when the weather turns saves a repair bill.
        If a pipe has already failed once in the cold, it will fail again —
        fix the cause, not just the joint.
      </p>

      <p>
        If you are in Galston and need something similar, Fraser will come
        and look for free. Call <strong>07900 255876</strong> or WhatsApp
        <strong>+44 7472 223323</strong>. FREE no-obligation quote, every job
        priced individually.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 rounded-2xl border border-navy-900/10 bg-navy-50/50 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-navy-900/60">Written by</p>
        <p class="mt-1 font-serif text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">{post.author}</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-navy-900/75 text-sm">{post.authorBio}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  {relatedPosts.length > 0 && (
    <RelatedPosts posts={relatedPosts} eyebrow="Keep reading" heading="Related posts" variant="tinted" />
  )}

  <CTABlock
    heading="Weep, drip or full-on leak?"
    sub="WhatsApp a photo with the water turned off and we will tell you how long a fix should take."
    location="Galston"
  />
</BaseLayout>
